                    <div class="row text-row">
                        <div class="col-lg-6">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What can microdermabrasion do for me?</h3>
                                <p>
                                    Skin that has sun damage, uneven tone, age spots, acne scars, fine lines, wrinkles, superficial scarring, and more benefit considerably.  Do you want a deep cleansing facial scrub? Then microdermabrasion is for you.  Another added perk is the way it minimizes and unclogs pores.  Safe on all skin types, and you will notice the effect of softer more supple skin after just one treatment. 
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>How often should I have microdermabrasion treatments?</h3>
                                <p>
                                    The results of microdermabrasion will look different for different people. Most will see smoother, healthier skin immediately, but many medical professionals advise having anywhere from 6-12 procedures done to get the full benefit of skin rejuvenation.  Our skilled specialists can recommend a program based on your needs and suggest treatments every few months to maintain optimal results.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-lg-6">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What can I expect from microdermabrasion?</h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    Safe, painless and convenient.  There are no needles or anesthesia.  Some people have compared the feeling from the exfoliating tool to a lick from a cat or a mild sunburn.  The session is performed in-office and could last anywhere from 30 to 60 minutes. To keep your eyes safe; protective eye coverings will be applied.  Afterward, some slight pinkness is considered normal and will dissipate in a few hours. Applying moisturizer helps alleviate this unpleasantness.  Some swelling and mild bruising can occur due to the suction power of the tool.  There is no downtime, and a person can be expected to go back to a normal routine immediately.  
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>How do I prepare for my microdermabrasion facial?</h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    Cleanse your face and make sure to eliminate all makeup.  Avoid tanning creams, waxing and exposure to the sun for about a week before treatment.  Also, some experts advise stopping the use of exfoliating creams and masks a few days before. Skin conditions like rosacea, eczema, dermatitis or psoriasis, are not good candidates for this type of skin-resurfacing.  One of our experts can help answer any questions and help decide what is best in your situation.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
